One might try to improve the precision of the perturbative calculation by letting $H^{(0)}$ contain higher-order terms, like for the ``simplex of complete graphs'' in \cite{Wong7,Wong9,Wong16}. In our case, however, including both terms that scale as $\Theta(n)$ and $\Theta(\sqrt{n})$ in $H^{(0)}$ yields a matrix, equivalent to \fref{fig:diagram_H0H1}, whose eigensystem is still too messy to determine.



